Sure, here are several example sentences in Serbian that use the word "diše" in different forms and positions, with the word highlighted with a star (*) and English translations in parentheses:

1. On *diše* duboko dok trči. (He breathes deeply while running.)
2. Čim uđem u ovu prostoriju, *diše* mi se teško. (As soon as I enter this room, I find it hard to breathe.)
3. Ona *diše* miris cvijeća. (She breathes in the smell of flowers.)
4. Vjetar *diše* kroz grane drveća. (The wind breathes through the branches of the trees.)
5. Svako jutro meditiram kako bih lakše *disao*. (I meditate every morning to breathe easier.)
6. Kad god sam uzbuđen, *disanje* mi se ubrza. (Whenever I'm excited, my breathing speeds up.)
7. Njegovo *disanje* je bilo jako slabo nakon nesreće. (His breathing was very weak after the accident.)
8. Molim te, prestani *disati* tako jako. (Please stop breathing so loudly.)